-- Dr. Reddy's, Maytas Infra, Sun Pharma and Rajasthan: India Equity Preview
-- Abhishek Shanker
-- 2010-06-21T02:59:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-21/dr-reddy-s-maytas-infra-sun-pharma-and-rajasthan-india-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
 unusual  price changes in India  trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the  last close .  
 The Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive Index, or  Sensex , fell
45.87, or 0.3 percent, to 17,570.82, the S&P CNX  Nifty  Index on
the National Stock Exchange declined 0.2 percent to 5,262.60 and
the  BSE 200 Index  decreased 0.4 percent to 2,215.67. SGX CNX
Nifty Index futures for June delivery rose 1.1 percent to
5,316.5 at 10:50 a.m. in Singapore.  
 Bank of Rajasthan Ltd.  (BOR IN): The bank’s employees may
strike for three days from today, the bank said in an
advertisement in the Economic Times newspaper. The employees are
protesting a proposed merger with ICICI Bank Ltd., it said. Bank
of Rajasthan fell 1.2 percent to 171.95 rupees. ICICI Bank
declined 1.7 percent to 869.3 rupees.  
 Dr. Reddy’s Laboratories Ltd.  (DRRD IN): The drugmaker may
sell a stake in its domestic formulations business after
demerging it, the Business Standard newspaper reported. The
shares fell 0.1 percent 1,421.70 rupees.  
 Hindalco Industries Ltd.  (HNDL IN): The company’s unit
Novelis Inc. may bid for the rolled products division of Rio
Tinto Alcan, The Economic Times reported, citing people familiar
with the development. A Hindalco spokesman declined to comment
and there was no response to an e-mail sent to Rio Tinto Alcan,
the newspaper said. Hindalco declined 1 percent to 145.35 rupees.  
 Infrastructure Development Finance Co. Ltd.  (IDFC IN): The
company plans to take a global fund manager as a strategic
partner in its asset management unit, India’s Economic Times
reported, citing executive director Vikram Limaye. IDFC rose 2.8
percent to 169 rupees.  
 Maytas Infra Ltd.  (MAY IN): The infrastructure developer
will sell a 20 percent stake to Saudi Binladin Group’s SBG
Projects Investments Ltd., the Indian company said in a
statement on its website. The shares fell 2.5 percent to 210.95
rupees.  
 Schrader Duncan Ltd.  (SDL IN): Schrader Bridgeport
International Inc. is in talks with industrialist J.P. Goenka to
buy his 24 percent stake in the joint venture company, Press
Trust of India reported without saying where it got the
information. The shares rose 1.5 percent to 165.90 rupees.  
 Sun Pharmaceutical Industries Ltd.  (SUNP IN): The nation’s
largest drugmaker by market value has secured approval from the
U.S. Food and Drug Administration to market a generic version of
Pfizer Inc.’s Xanax, it said in an e-mailed statement. The
shares rose 0.9 percent to 1,713.35 rupees.  
 Titan Industries Ltd.  (TTAN IN): The company’s jewelry
brand Tanishq expects to see retail sales increase by 30 percent
this fiscal year driven by expansion in India, the Financial
Chronicle said, citing Sandeep Kulhalli, vice president retail
for Tanishq. Titan fell 0.1 percent to 2,197.4 rupees.  
 With assistance from Berni Moestafa in Jakarta. Editor: Margo
Towie  
